Video 4 — Strings

Overview:
Strings are sequences of characters. Supports indexing, slicing, concatenation, and formatting. Essential for I/O and text processing.

Key Concepts:

f-strings for readable formatting
String methods: .upper(), .lower(), .replace()

Example:

name = "Alice"
greeting = f"Hello, {name}!"
print(greeting)

Practical Insights:

Strings are crucial in reporting, user interaction, and data parsing
